  "response": "Rockville and Laytonsville are both located in Montgomery County, Maryland, but they have some distinct differences:\n\nRockville:\n- Larger city with around 68,000 residents\n- More urban environment\n- Better public transportation\n- More diverse job market\n- Higher median household income (around $110,000)\n- More amenities, shopping, and dining options\n- Excellent public schools\n- Higher cost of living\n\nLaytonsville:\n- Small, rural community with around 1,500 residents\n- More suburban/rural setting\n- Less dense population\n- Fewer amenities and services\n- More spacious properties and land\n- Lower cost of living\n- More agricultural and historic character\n- Quieter and more serene environment\n\nBoth areas are considered safe and have good quality of life, but they offer very different living experiences. Rockville provides more urban conveniences, while Laytonsville offers a more tranquil, countryside atmosphere. The choice between them depends on personal preferences regarding lifestyle, work, and community.",
